{{Orphan|date=July 2013}}

A '''barn cleaner''' is a device used to aid in the cleaning of [[tie-stall barn|tie-stall]] and [[stanchion barn]]s. It usually consists of a series of paddles [[chain link]]ed together, that move [[manure]] and other waste through a gutter and into a [[manure spreader]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.epa.gov/agriculture/ag101/dairyglossary.html | title=Dairy Glossary | publisher=Environmental Protection Agency | work=Ag 101 | accessdate=July 7, 2013}}</ref>

