{{Other uses|Techne (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox journal | title = Techné: Research in Philosophy and Technology | cover = techne-cov.gif | editor = Neelke Doorn and Diane P. Michelfelder | discipline = [[Philosophy]] | formernames = Society for Philosophy and Technology Quarterly Electronic Journal | abbreviation = | publisher = [[Philosophy Documentation Center]] | country = United States | frequency = Triannual | history = 1995–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.pdcnet.org/techne | link2 = http://www.pdcnet.org/techne/toc | link2-name = Online access | link3 = http://www.pdcnet.org/pdc/bvdb.nsf/journaldetail?openform&journal=pdc_techne&cat=special | link3-name = Special issues | JSTOR = | OCLC = 150404086 | LCCN = 96-2725 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1091-8264 }} '''''Techné: Research in Philosophy and Technology''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] with a focus on [[Philosophy|philosophical]] analysis of technological systems. The journal was established in 1995 as an electronic journal, under the sponsorship of the [[Society for Philosophy and Technology]]. It is published three times per year and online access to the journal is a benefit of membership in the society. The journal is published for the society by the [[Philosophy Documentation Center]]. The current [[editor-in-chief|editors-in-chief]] are Neelke Doorn and Diane P. Michelfelder.
